  <h1>
   <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Sequences/i_sequence_pause.png"/><br/>
   Play Sequence
  </h1>
  With this action you can pause a playing sequence. You supply the sequence element ID (as returned by the action
  <a href="Create_Sequence_Element.htm">
   Create Sequence
  </a>
  ), and the action will pause it playing.
  <h4>
   Action Syntax:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Sequences/a_sequence_pause.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Arguments:
  </h4>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      Variable
     </td>
     <td>
      The ID of the sequence element to pause.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Sequences/e_sequence_play.png"/><br/>
  The above action block code checks to see if a global variable is
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  .
    If it is then the sequence element referenced in the variable "
  <span>
   my_seq
  </span>
  " is paused, otherwise it is set to play.
 </body>
